{"title_page": "Naran (town)", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=January 2018}}\n\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n| name                    = Naran\n| native_name             = {{nq|\u0646\u0627\u0631\u0627\u0646}}\n| native_name_lang        = ur\n| settlement_type         = [[Town]]\n| image_skyline           = File:Entrance of Naran..jpg \n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = Naran Town\n| ag              = \n| flag_alt                = \n| image_seal              = \n| seal_alt                = \n| image_shield            = \n| shield_alt              = \n| nickname                = \n| motto                   = \n| image_map               = \n| map_alt                 = \n| map_caption             = \n| pushpin_map             = Khyber Pakhtunkhwa#Pakistan\n| pushpin_label_position  = left\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = \n| coordinates             = {{Coord|34|54|22|N|73|38|58|E|type:city_region:PK|display=inline,title}}\n| coor_pinpoint           = \n| coordinates_footnotes   = \n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = {{flagicon|PAK}}[[Pakistan]]\n| subdivision_type1       = [[Provinces of Pakistan|Province]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of districts of Pakistan|District]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Mansehra District|Mansehra]]\n| subdivision_type3       = \n| subdivision_name3       = \n| established_title       = \n| established_date        = \n| founder                 = \n| seat_type               = \n| seat                    = \n| government_footnotes    = \n| leader_party            = \n| leader_title            = \n| leader_name             = \n| unit_pref               = Metric<!-- or US or UK -->\n<!-- ALL fields with measurements have automatic unit conversion -->\n<!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| area_footnotes          = \n| area_urban_footnotes    = <!-- <ref> </ref> -->\n| area_rural_footnotes    = <!-- <ref> </ref> -->\n| area_metro_footnotes    = <!-- <ref> </ref> -->\n| area_magnitude          = <!-- <ref> </ref> -->\n| area_note               = \n| area_water_percent      = \n| area_rank               = \n| area_blank1_title       = \n| area_blank2_title       = \n<!-- square kilometers -->\n| area_total_km2          = \n| area_land_km2           = \n| area_water_km2          = \n| area_urban_km2          = \n| area_rural_km2          = \n| area_metro_km2          = \n| area_blank1_km2         = \n| area_blank2_km2         = \n<!-- hectares -->\n| area_total_ha           = \n| area_land_ha            = \n| area_water_ha           = \n| area_urban_ha           = \n| area_rural_ha           = \n| area_metro_ha           = \n| area_blank1_ha          = \n| area_blank2_ha          = \n<!-- dunams used in Middle East articles only -->\n| dunam_link              = <!-- which dunam to link -->\n| area_total_dunam        = \n| area_land_dunam         = \n| area_water_dunam        = \n| area_urban_dunam        = \n| area_rural_dunam        = \n| area_metro_dunam        = \n| area_blank1_dunam       = \n| area_blank2_dunam       = \n| length_km               = \n| width_km                = \n| dimensions_footnotes    = \n| elevation_footnotes     = \n| elevation_m             = 2409\n| population_footnotes    = \n| population_total        = \n| population_as_of        = \n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      = \n| population_note         = \n| timezone1               = [[Pakistan Standard Time|PST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +5\n| timezone1_DST           = \n| utc_offset1_DST         = \n| postal_code_type        = \n| postal_code             = 21200\n| area_code_type          = \n| area_code               = \n| iso_code                = \n| website                 = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| footnotes               = \n| blank_name              = [[National Highways of Pakistan|Highways]]\n| blank_info              = {{jct|country=pk|N|15}}\n}}\n'''Naran''' ({{lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|'''\u0646\u0627\u0631\u0627\u0646''' }}}}) is a medium-sized town in upper [[Kaghan Valley]] in [[Mansehra District]] of [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]] province of [[Pakistan]]. It is located {{convert|119|km|mi|sp=us}} from [[Mansehra|Mansehra city]] at the altitude of {{convert|2409|m|ft|sp=us}}.It is located about {{convert|65|km|mi|sp=us}} away from [[Babusar Top]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Naran on map |url=https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Babusar+Pass/Naran,+Mansehra,+Khyber+Pakhtunkhwa |website=[[Google Maps]] |accessdate=13 September 2019}}</ref> It is a popular tourist attraction locally as well as internationally.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://narankaghan.pk/naran-kaghan-top-10-breathtaking-views-must-see-places/|title=Top 10 Breathtaking views & Must See Places in Naran Kaghan|date=2018-05-29|website=narankaghan.pk|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-09}}</ref>\n\nNaran became a popular tourist spot in 2012, After the complete end of [[Taliban]] from Pakistan. If you are travelling form Islamabad to [[Gilgit-Baltistan]] by road Naran should be the point to stop. \n\n== Tourism In Naran ==\nNaran Kaghan is famous as a tourist destination, owing to its pleasant weather in peak season every year thousands of tourists rush to explore the valley. It is also the gateway to Gilgit Hunza in Summers by Babusar Pass. Naran Bazaar is very crowded in summers with hotels and restaurants offering their services. [https://www.pakistantravelguide.pk/tours/naran-kaghan-tour/ Naran Kaghan Tour] is a Pakistani dream for those living in big cities like Karachi, Lahore and Islamabad. In 2020, government expects that 5 million tourists will explore the valley.{{Citation needed|reason=without citation, just an editors guess|date=February 2020}}\n\n==Weather==\n[[File:Burawai near Naran.jpg|thumb|left|The surrounding Kaghan Valley]]\n[[File:Northern Pakistan 18.JPG|thumb|left|A view over the town]]\nNaran has a [[humid continental climate]] ([[K\u00f6ppen climate classification|Koppen Climate Classification]] ''Dfb'').<ref name=\"Climate-Data.org\"/> There is significant rainfall in summers and heavy snowfall in winters. However the trend is changing due to climate change within the region, and for the past few years, Naran is receiving lesser snowfall. It is advisable to visit Naran in the month of January to watch and enjoy snow falling there. It is a famous summer destination for people who come here from within Pakistan and abroad to enjoy the weather. The temperature, though, is rising. A few years back, Naran was only accessible in June, but for a few years, accessibility is improving, and the roads are drive-able even in early spring. Naran remains busy in summer, starting earlier, and tourism is extending up to late in the fall. The average annual temperature in Naran is 10.1 \u00b0C. The region is Alpine in geography and climate, with forests and meadows dominating the landscape below peaks that reach over 17,000 feet.\n\n{{Weather box\n|metric first=yes\n|single line=yes\n|location=Naran, Kaghan Valley\n|Jan record high C=11\n|Feb record high C=15\n|Mar record high C=21\n|Apr record high C=30\n|May record high C=35\n|Jun record high C=32\n|Jul record high C=32\n|Aug record high C=32\n|Sep record high C=34\n|Oct record high C=31\n|Nov record high C=19\n|Dec record high C=15\n\n|year record high C= 32\n\n|Jan high C=-0.2\n|Feb high C=3.5\n|Mar high C=8.3\n|Apr high C=14.4\n|May high C=19.4\n|Jun high C=24.6\n|Jul high C=25.2\n|Aug high C=24.3\n|Sep high C=21.7\n|Oct high C=17.4\n|Nov high C=11.6\n|Dec high C=4\n\n|Jan mean C=-2.3\n|Feb mean C=-2\n|Mar mean C=3.3\n|Apr mean C=10\n|May mean C=14.1\n|Jun mean C=18.9\n|Jul mean C=19.8\n|Aug mean C=19.3\n|Sep mean C=16.2\n|Oct mean C=11.9\n|Nov mean C=6.6\n|Dec mean C=1.5\n\n|Jan low C=-6\n|Feb low C=-4\n|Mar low C=0\n|Apr low C=5.6\n|May low C=8.9\n|Jun low C=13.3\n|Jul low C=14.5\n|Aug lo