| next_year = 1996\n| election_date = November 3, 1992\n| image_size = x160px\n| image1 = Bill Clinton.jpg\n| nominee1 = '''[[Bill Clinton]]'''\n| party1 = Democratic Party (United States)\n| home_state1 = [[Arkansas]]\n| running_mate1 = '''[[Al Gore]]'''\n| electoral_vote1 = '''11'''\n| popular_vote1 = '''993,037'''\n| percentage1 = '''43.41%'''\t\n| image2 = George H. W. Bush, President of the United States, 1989 official portrait (cropped 2).jpg\n| nominee2 = [[George H.W. Bush]] \n| party2 = Republican Party (United States)\n| home_state2 = [[Texas]]\n| running_mate2 = [[Dan Quayle]]\n| electoral_vote2 = 0\n| popular_vote2 = 731,234\n| percentage2 = 31.97%\t\n| image3 = RossPerotColor.jpg\n| nominee3 = [[Ross Perot]]\n| party3 = Independent (politician)\n| home_state3 = [[Texas]]\n| running_mate3 = [[James Stockdale]]\n| electoral_vote3 = 0\n| popular_vote3 = 541,780\t\n| percentage3 = 23.68%\n| map_image = 1992 United States Presidential election in Washington (state).svg\n| map_size = 350px\n| map_caption = County Results\n{{col-start}}\n{{col-2}}\n'''Clinton'''\n{{legend|#d3e7ff|<40%}}\n{{legend|#b9d7ff|40-50%}}\n{{legend|#86b6f2|50-60%}}\n{{col-2}}\n'''Bush'''\n{{legend|#ffccd0|<40%}}\n{{legend|#f2b3be|40-50%}}\n{{col-end}}\n| title = President\n| before_election = [[George H. W. Bush]]\n| before_party = Republican Party (United States)\n| after_election = [[Bill Clinton]]\n| after_party = Democratic Party (United States)\n}}\n\n{{ElectionsWA}}\n\nThe '''1992 United States presidential election in Washington''' took place on November 3, 1992, as part of the [[1992 United States presidential election]]. Voters chose eleven representatives, or electors to the [[United States Electoral College|Electoral College]], who voted for [[President of the United States|president]] and [[Vice President of the United States|vice president]].\n\n[[United States presidential elections in Washington|Washington]] was won by Governor [[Bill Clinton]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]]-[[Arkansas]]) with 43.41% of the popular vote over incumbent President [[George H. W. Bush|George H.W. Bush]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|R]]\u2013[[Texas]]) with 31.97%. Businessman [[Ross Perot]] ([[Independent politician|I]]-Texas) finished in third, with 23.68% of the popular vote.<ref name=results/> Clinton ultimately won the national vote, defeating incumbent President Bush.<ref>{{cite web|title=1992 Presidential General Election Results|url=http://uselectionatlas.org/RESULTS/national.php?year=1992|publisher=U.S. Election Atlas|accessdate=11 June 2012}}</ref> {{As of|2016|11|alt=As of [[2016 United States presidential election in Washington (state)|the 2016 presidential election]]}}, this was the last election in which [[Okanogan County, Washington|Okanogan County]] voted for a Democratic Presidential nominee.<ref name=\"how\">Sullivan, Robert David; [http://www.americamagazine.org/content/unconventional-wisdom/how-red-and-blue-map-evolved-over-past-century \u2018How the Red and Blue Map Evolved Over the Past Century\u2019]; ''America Magazine'' in ''The National Catholic Review''; June 29, 2016</ref> It was also the first occasion since [[Franklin D. Roosevelt]]\u2019s 1936 landslide that [[Whitman County, Washington|Whitman County]] had supported a Democratic presidential candidate.<ref name=\"Geography\">Menendez, Albert J.; ''The Geography of Presidential Elections in the United States, 1868-2004'', pp. 332-334 {{ISBN|0786422173}}</ref>\n\n==Results==\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|- style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"\n! colspan=\"6\" | 1992 United States presidential election in Washington<ref name=results>{{cite web|title=1992 Presidential General Election Results - Washington|url=http://uselectionatlas.org/RESULTS/state.php?year=1992&fips=53&f=0&off=0&elect=0&minper=0|publisher=U.S. Electi